summary:
Let $X$ be a projective algebraic manifold and let $CH^r(X)$ be the Chow group of algebraic cycles of codimension $r$ on $X$, modulo rational equivalence. Working with a candidate Bloch-Beilinson filtration $\{F^{
u}\}_{
u\geq 0}$ on $CH^r(X)\otimes {\Bbb Q}$ due to the second author, we construct a space of arithmetic Hodge theoretic invariants $
abla J^{r,
u}(X)$ and corresponding map $\phi_{X}^{r,
u} : Gr_{F}^{
u}CH^r(X)\otimes {\Bbb Q} 	o 
abla J^{r,
u}(X)$, and determine conditions on $X$ for which the kernel and image of $\phi_{X}^{r,
u}$ are ``uncountably large''.
